$ Oracle: DBA_STATEMENTS

`dba_statements` lists → development/databases/Oracle/SQL/statement[SQL statements] that are found in PL/SQL objects.

This → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary view comes in all four variants:
`user_statements`, `all_statements`, `dba_statements` and `cdb_statements`.

In order for this view to be populated with the information about statements, the → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters[init parameter]
→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/plscope_settings[`plscope_settings`]
must be set to `statements:all`.

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary/identifiers[`dba_identifiers`]

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/data-dictionary
